+
+<section class="card">
+<span class="pill">Release 218 · Browser-generated output</span>
+<h1 class="section-title" lang="ta">அச்சு மற்றும் PDF ஆதரவு</h1>
+<h2>Print and PDF Support</h2>
+<p>Published pages now load a shared print layer. Use the page-level “Print / Save PDF” control, then choose your browser or operating system’s PDF destination when required.</p>
+<p><button class="btn" type="button" onclick="window.print()">Print this guide / Save PDF</button></p>
+</section>
+
+<section class="print-pdf-grid" aria-label="Print workflow">
+<article class="card print-pdf-step">
+<span class="pill">Step 1</span>
+<strong>Open the required published page</strong>
+<span>Use Search Facets, the reading list, Explore or the site directory to reach the exact route.</span>
+</article>
+<article class="card print-pdf-step">
+<span class="pill">Step 2</span>
+<strong>Select “Print / Save PDF”</strong>
+<span>The browser print dialog opens. Navigation, buttons, forms, audio controls and decorative shadows are removed from the printed copy.</span>
+</article>
+<article class="card print-pdf-step">
+<span class="pill">Step 3</span>
+<strong>Choose paper or PDF</strong>
+<span>Select a physical printer or a destination such as “Save as PDF” or “Microsoft Print to PDF”.</span>
+</article>
+<article class="card print-pdf-step">
+<span class="pill">Step 4</span>
+<strong>Review before saving</strong>
+<span>Confirm page range, paper size, orientation and Tamil text rendering before printing or creating the PDF.</span>
+</article>
+</section>
+
+<section class="card">
+<h2>Print output improvements</h2>
+<ul>
+<li>Print-only title and canonical-source header.</li>
+<li>White background, black text and reduced visual decoration.</li>
+<li>Navigation, forms, buttons, media players and update notices excluded.</li>
+<li>Responsive images and printable tables.</li>
+<li>Readable code wrapping and underlined links.</li>
+<li>Existing Tamil and English content is not rewritten.</li>
+</ul>
+</section>
+
+<section class="card print-pdf-boundary">
+<h2>Important boundary</h2>
+<p>This release does not generate or host PDF files on a server. It provides clean print styling and invokes the browser print dialog. A browser-created PDF is a convenience copy of the displayed route; it does not change the route’s source status, review status, completeness or copyright position.</p>
+<p>No claim is made that every browser, printer driver, font installation or assistive technology produces identical pagination.</p>
+</section>
+
+<noscript><section class="card" role="status"><h2>JavaScript is disabled</h2><p>Use the browser menu or press Ctrl+P / Command+P. The print stylesheet still applies when it has loaded from this page.</p></section></noscript>
+</main>
